The paper describes a fully data-driven model that uses recurrent neural networks to perform a sequence-to-sequence mapping task for retrosynthetic reaction prediction. This task involves predicting the reactants that can be used to synthesize a given product molecule. The paper uses a large dataset of experimental reaction examples and compares the performance of the model with a rule-based expert system baseline model. Given the focus on machine learning and natural language processing techniques, as well as the use of neural networks, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves image processing techniques for chemical structures, which could fall under cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
